<!--
  PROFILE CUSTOM TABS SNIPPET

  Adds the "SOUL" tab to the character profile page tab list.

  FILE: ares-webportal/app/components/profile-custom-tabs.hbs

  INSTALLATION:

  1. Open your game's ares-webportal/app/components/profile-custom-tabs.hbs
  2. Copy the code block below this comment:
     - If the file is empty or nearly empty, paste it as-is.
     - If the file already has other tabs, add it after another tab's
       closing </li>.

  IMPORTANT:
  - Do not change href="#soul-tab-pane". It must match the pane id in
    profile-custom.snippet.hbs.
  - Install custom_char_fields.snippet.rb before using this block. The
    custom fields provide the enabled, approval, and staff checks below.
  - If your game reuses different shared field names for is_approved or
    viewer_id, update this snippet and profile-custom.snippet.hbs to match.
  - The web portal integration is optional. MUSH commands work without it.
-->

{{#if (and this.char.custom.soul_enabled (or this.char.custom.is_approved this.char.custom.can_manage_soul))}}
  <li class="nav-item">
    <a class="nav-link" data-bs-toggle="tab" href="#soul-tab-pane">SOUL</a>
  </li>
{{/if}}
